<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" version="2.0"><channel><title>Lafuente (autofs)</title><link>http://lafuente.me/</link><description></description><atom:link rel="self" href="http://lafuente.me/tags/autofs.xml" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 21 Apr 2015 12:05:58 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>http://getnikola.com/</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>Autofs configuration</title><link>http://lafuente.me/posts/autofs-configuration.html</link><dc:creator>Jos√© Luis Lafuente</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Autofs uses &lt;cite&gt;/etc/autofs/auto.master&lt;/cite&gt; as its default primary configuration
file. We can define two kind of maps in this file, direct and indirect. An
example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code text"&gt;&lt;a name="rest_code_fa4b6627f10541a2a864fe04dc50e803-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;# mount point   config file        options
&lt;a name="rest_code_fa4b6627f10541a2a864fe04dc50e803-2"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;/-              /etc/autofs/auto.direct   --ghost
&lt;a name="rest_code_fa4b6627f10541a2a864fe04dc50e803-3"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;/media/cifs     /etc/autofs/auto.cifs     --timeout=60 --ghost
&lt;a name="rest_code_fa4b6627f10541a2a864fe04dc50e803-4"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;/media/sshfs    /etc/autofs/auto.sshfs    --timeout=60 --ghost
&lt;a name="rest_code_fa4b6627f10541a2a864fe04dc50e803-5"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;+auto.master
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p class="more"&gt;&lt;a href="http://lafuente.me/posts/autofs-configuration.html"&gt; &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>autofs</category><category>linux</category><guid>http://lafuente.me/posts/autofs-configuration.html</guid><pubDate>Fri, 11 Mar 2011 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>